field.value:
The tenant Administrator is able to make tenant specific configurations - like date format, number of items per page in the search result, automatic session expiry logout time, etc.

For Administrators there is an Admin Menu in the Main menu.

Rules:

  • In the Admin Menu there is System Configuration option.
  • When the option is selected then a screen opens with the available configurations with their current values.

    • Tenant configurations filtering by keyword is available.

  • Each of the default configurations could be manually edited.
  • For each configuration there is a field matching the configuration type - i.e. for dates there is a calendar, for integers there is a field allowing only integer values, etc.
  • When the new configurations are saved, they are automatically applied to the system.

Example: Change the default configurations for maximum pages displayed in the search results and the maximum results from search per page.

  • The user clicks on the Admin menu (1) and selects the System Configuration option (2).

 

  • The screen with the available configurations with their current values opens (1).
  • The configurations are displayed in alphabetical order, collapsed (2).
  • The filtering by keyword option (3-4) is displayed above the configurations.
  • The user may scroll (5) and search for the configuration groups.

 

 

  • The user enters text (here - search) in the keyword field (1) and clicks Filter (2).
    • The user expands the necessary configuration group (here - Search) (3).
    • The group/s with configurations in which the text is found either in the name of the group (3) or in the configuration itself (4) are displayed.
  • In front of each configuration there is a sign "i" (5). When the user hovers the mouse over it then a short information about the configuration is displayed.
  • For each configuration there is a field matching the configuration type and format (6,7).
  • The options Save (8) and Cancel (9) are at the bottom of the screen.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

  • The user changes the necessary configurations and clicks "Save".
  • The system displays a confirmation message  with text "Saving potentially incorrect configurations might harm the environment, are you sure you want to proceed? Configurations that are modified: "
    • The modified configurations (2) are listed.
  • The user clicks Yes (3).
  • The changed configurations are applied in the system.
